## Core Principles (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
1. Raw PII must NEVER leave the local machine.
2. Raw uploaded files are stored ENCRYPTED (AES-256-GCM) on disk at all times.
3. The anonymization map (placeholder → original) is NEVER sent to the frontend,
   cloud, or any log.
4. Anonymization is session-scoped and includes coreference resolution.
5. File type is detected by content (python-magic), never by extension.
6. Septum is GLOBALLY generic: it is NOT tied to any single country, language,
   or regulation. It works across all jurisdictions, all languages, and allows
   users to define custom rules on top of built-in ones.
7. No static query or document logic: retrieval, prompts, and fallbacks must
   not hardcode question phrases, document labels, or question-type detection;
   handle all user questions and content generically.
8. No unnecessary comments in classes or methods; docstrings are required,
   but redundant, obvious, or decorative comments must be avoided.
9. UI language: User-facing content may be fully localized. The default language is English, and additional languages (including Turkish) can be provided via an i18n system. All explanation messages, error text, and field labels must use the active UI language selected by the user.
10. All backend LLM/Ollama prompts MUST be managed centrally via a prompt catalog (for example, `backend/app/services/prompts.py` and `PromptCatalog`); new prompts are added there and existing prompts are updated only through this catalog, never as ad-hoc inline strings in services or routers.



