## Global Privacy Regulation Engine

### Philosophy
Septum ships with a built-in registry of known privacy regulations.
Each regulation is a named ruleset (a collection of entity types + detection rules).
Users activate one or more rulesets. Multiple rulesets can be combined.
Users can also create fully custom rulesets with their own entity definitions.
The sanitizer always runs the union of all active rulesets.

### Built-in Regulation Registry

Septum ships with pre-built recognizer packs for the following regulations.
Each pack is a Python module in: services/recognizers/{regulation_id}/

| Regulation ID  | Name                                  | Region            |
|----------------|---------------------------------------|-------------------|
| gdpr           | General Data Protection Regulation    | EU / EEA          |
| kvkk           | Kişisel Verileri Koruma Kanunu        | Turkey            |
| ccpa           | California Consumer Privacy Act       | USA (California)  |
| cpra           | California Privacy Rights Act         | USA (California)  |
| hipaa          | Health Insurance Portability Act      | USA (Healthcare)  |
| pipeda         | Personal Information Protection Act   | Canada            |
| lgpd           | Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados        | Brazil            |
| pdpa_th        | Personal Data Protection Act          | Thailand          |
| pdpa_sg        | Personal Data Protection Act          | Singapore         |
| appi           | Act on Protection of Personal Info    | Japan             |
| pipl           | Personal Information Protection Law   | China             |
| popia          | Protection of Personal Information    | South Africa      |
| dpdp           | Digital Personal Data Protection Act  | India             |
| uk_gdpr        | UK GDPR (post-Brexit)                 | United Kingdom    |
| pdpl_sa        | Personal Data Protection Law          | Saudi Arabia      |
| nzpa           | Privacy Act 2020                      | New Zealand       |
| australia_pa   | Privacy Act 1988 (amended)            | Australia         |

### Per-Regulation Entity Types

Each regulation pack declares which entity types it enforces.
Below is the global master entity type list.
Each regulation activates a subset.

IDENTITY:
