## Language & NER Support

Septum is fully multilingual. Language detection is automatic.

### Language Detection
Use `langdetect` (or `lingua-language-detector` for higher accuracy) to detect
the language of each document and each user query automatically.
Detected language is stored in document metadata.
Users can override the detected language per-document in the UI.

### NER Models — Language-Aware Loading
Load NER models based on detected language.
All models run device-aware (get_device(): CUDA → MPS → CPU).
Use quantized INT8 variants on CPU.

Language → Model mapping (configurable in Settings, these are defaults):

| Language         | Model                                       |
|------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| English          | dslim/bert-base-NER                         |
| Turkish          | savasy/bert-base-turkish-ner-cased          |
| German           | dbmdz/bert-large-cased-finetuned-conll03-german |
| French           | Jean-Baptiste/roberta-large-ner-english     |
| Spanish          | mrm8488/bert-spanish-cased-finetuned-ner    |
| Dutch            | wietsedv/bert-base-dutch-cased-finetuned-ner|
| Chinese          | uer/roberta-base-finetuned-cluener2020-chinese |
| Arabic           | hatmimoha/arabic-ner-bert                   |
| Russian          | DeepPavlov/rubert-base-cased-ner            |
| Portuguese       | malduwais/biobert-base-cased-v1.2-finetuned-ner |
| Japanese         | cl-tohoku/bert-base-japanese (+ custom NER) |
| Multilingual     | Babelscape/wikineural-multilingual-ner      |
| Fallback (any)   | Babelscape/wikineural-multilingual-ner      |

Model loading strategy:
  - Load the language-specific model if available in registry.
  - Fall back to Babelscape/wikineural-multilingual-ner for unsupported languages.
  - Models are loaded lazily (on first use) and cached in memory.
  - Users can add custom model mappings in Settings (Settings → NER Models tab).

### Presidio Language Support
Presidio's AnalyzerEngine supports multiple languages.
Register recognizers for: en, tr, de, fr, es, it, pt, nl, zh, ar, ru, ja, ko, pl, sv.
For languages without specific recognizers: use the multilingual NER model as fallback.
Users can add new language recognizer packs via Settings.

### OCR Language Support (EasyOCR)
EasyOCR supports 80+ languages.
Default OCR languages: ["en"] (user configures in Settings → Ingestion).
User can select any combination from the full EasyOCR language list.
Document-level language override available in Documents page.

### Whisper Audio Transcription
Whisper auto-detects language — no configuration needed for most cases.
Language override available per-document if auto-detection is incorrect.

### ID Number Validation — Country-Specific Algorithms
Implement algorithmic validation (not just regex) for the following national IDs.
Each is a separate Recognizer class in services/recognizers/:

  Turkey   TCKN      — 11-digit Luhn-like checksum (d10, d11 formula)
  USA      SSN       — format 3-2-4, blacklist 000/666/900-999 area codes
  Germany  Steuer-ID — 11-digit, first digit 1-9, Luhn mod 11 variant
  France   NIR       — 15 digits, sex + birth year + department + checksum
  UK       NINO      — regex: [A-CEGHJ-PR-TW-Z]{2}[0-9]{6}[A-D]
  Brazil   CPF       — 11 digits, two-step Luhn checksum
  India    Aadhaar   — 12 digits, Verhoeff checksum
  China    RIC       — 18 chars, GB11643 checksum
  Japan    My Number — 12 digits, checksum validation
  South Korea RRN   — 13 digits, checksum mod 11
  Netherlands BSN   — 9 digits, 11-proef checksum
  Australia TFN     — 8-9 digits, weighted checksum
  Canada   SIN       — 9 digits, Luhn algorithm
  Mexico   CURP      — 18-char alphanumeric, regex + format validation
  Argentina DNI     — 7-8 digit national ID, format validation
  IBAN (global)     — country prefix + checksum (ISO 7064 MOD 97-10)
  SWIFT/BIC         — 8-11 char, ISO 9362 format validation
  Passport (generic)— country code + alphanumeric, format per ICAO Doc 9303

For countries not listed: use generic NATIONAL_ID pattern (8-12 digit sequence
with context words: ["kimlik", "ID", "national", "citizen", "passport", etc.])

